from fractions import Fraction

def total_rows(p, q, n, r, s):
    p_q = Fraction(p, q)
    r_s = Fraction(r, s)
    if p_q != r_s:
        return 'The input fractions are the same.'
    rows_already_knitted = n / (p_q - r_s)
    total_rows = rows_already_knitted + rows_already_knitted * p_q
    return total_rows
